# Playwright (Chromium + native deps) is now installed in nixpacks.toml's
# install phase, which is properly cached. The previous `release:` step
# that ran `playwright install-deps` + `playwright install chromium` on
# every deploy has been removed because:
#   - It executed in an uncached Docker layer (after `COPY . /app/.`),
#     so every deploy re-downloaded ~300 Ubuntu apt packages + ~170 MB
#     of Chromium, frequently timing out the build.
#   - DB migrations should be run intentionally, not on every restart.
#
# How to run a one-off DB migration on Railway:
#   railway run --service <service> python3 <migration_script>.py
# or from the Railway shell.
web:     python3 app.py
# Daily cron job for Manual AI analysis (schedule configured in Railway dashboard)
cron:    python3 daily_analysis_cron.py
